. I think I found the issue:

the method at line 256 of [_HoloActivity](https://github.com/ChristopheVersieux/HoloEverywhere/blob/master/library/src/android/support/v4/app/_HoloActivity.java)

``` java
@Override
    public void onCreateContextMenu(ContextMenu menu, View view,
            ContextMenuInfo menuInfo) {
        if (menu instanceof ContextMenuWrapper) {
            super.onCreateContextMenu(((ContextMenuWrapper) menu).unwrap(),
                    view, menuInfo);
        }
    }
```

in this case, menu is actually a `ContextMenuBuilder`, so the `if (menu instanceof ContextMenuWrapper)` statement fails and `super.onCreateContextMenu()` is never called. Unfortunately I can't figure out how to convert something from `ContextMenuBuilder` into `android.view.ContextMenu`.
. As a temporary workaround, setting: `Application.config().setDisableContextMenu(true);` in your application forces HoloEverywhere to use system context menus, so on ICS devices, you get the default context menus with rounded corners but this gets EditText context menus working. Don't forget to call the super `super.onCreateContextMenu(menu, v, menuInfo);` in your onCreateContextMenu.

You can see the code that affects this in: [`showContextMenuForChild` in ContextMenuDecorView](https://github.com/ChristopheVersieux/HoloEverywhere/blob/master/library/src/com/actionbarsherlock/internal/view/menu/ContextMenuDecorView.java#L102) is the offending function that returns a `ContextMenuBuilder`
